ActCanada Disability Savings Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Minister of Employment and Social Development, a Minister of the Crown, to be “the Minister” for the purposes of that Act
PrecisOrder (a) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2018-1021 of July 18, 2018; and (b) designating the MINISTER OF EMPLOYMENT AND SOCIAL DEVELOPMENT, a Minister of the Crown, to be "the Minister" for the purposes of the CANADA DISABILITY SAVINGS ACT.
